-- Kenya May Use `Substantial' Coal, Iron-Ore Deposits to Grow Steel Industry
-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 2010-10-20T08:19:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/kenya-may-use-substantial-coal-iron-ore-deposits-to-grow-steel-industry.html
Kenya has discovered “substantial”
deposits of coal and iron ore that may be processed commercially
to help develop a steel industry in the East African country,
President Mwai Kibaki said.  Kibaki commented in a prepared speech e-mailed from his
office in Nairobi, the capital, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  